Naa10 het heart

Naa10 heterozygous mutant (+/- or +/-) heart lysate analysis

Hearts were obtained from biological replicates of Naa10 heterozygous mutants (+/- or -/+; n = 3) and wild-type controls (+/+; n = 3). Each biological replicate was assayed twice.

Fresh or thawed flash-frozen tissue were lysed in RIPA buffer supplemented with protease inhibitor tablets (Sigma-Aldrich, #R0278; Roche #11836153001). Tissue was homogenized using a handheld motorized microtube pestle. Lysate was then cleared after centrifugation (15,000 rcf, 20 minutes). Total protein was quantified using Advanced Protein Assay Reagent (Cytoskeleton Inc., #ADV02). Lysate was then diluted in 2X SDS-PAGE Sample Buffer (5% v/v 2-mercaptoethanol) and heated (95 - 100C, 5 minutes).

20 g of protein were resolved on a a 10% mini-PROTEAN TGX gel (Bio-Rad, #4561033). SDS-PAGE gel was equilibrated in chilled Towbins transfer buffer. Proteins were transferred from gel to 0.2 m nitrocellulose membrane (Amersham) at 100V, 30 minutes under refrigeration. After transfer, membrane was allowed to dry at least 1 hour. Membranes were stained for transfer verification and total protein sing REVERT 700 total protein stain (Li-cor, #926-11015).

After stain removal, membrane was blocked in TBS with 5% non-fat dry milk (1 hr, RT). After decanting blocking buffer, membrane was incubated (overnight, 4C) in 1/500 anti-NAA10 (diluted in blocking buffer supplemented with 0.1% v/v Tween-20). Membrane was then washed 5 minutes in TBS-T for 3 repetitions. Membrane was then incubated (1 hr, RT) using 1/20000 goat-anti-rabbit IR800 CW (Li-cor, 926-32211). Membrane was again washed 5 minutes in TBS-T for 3 repetitions and then briefly rinsed in TBS. Membrane was allowed to dry before imaging.

Immunostained membranes were imaged on Odyssey Classic (Li-cor). Analysis was conducted and plotted using Empiria Studio (Li-cor) and R.

heart_sum1 <- summarySE(heart, measurevar="Normalized.Signal", groupvars=c("Genotype"))

heart_sum1
##    Genotype N Normalized.Signal       sd       se      ci
## 1 Naa10 +/- 6          74149.56 18452.58 7533.236 19364.8

#group means plus standards
#essentially looking to plot this onto the individual data plot
ggplot(heart_sum1, aes(x = Genotype, y = Normalized.Signal))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Normalized.Signal - sd,
                ymax = Normalized.Signal + sd))

###individual data and group means plot

#ggplot(heart) plots Normalized.Signal as a function of Genotype
#geom_point plots individual observations on this plot
#geom_errorbar points to my group means df heart_sum1 and the bounds of the mean+/- standard error bar
#the successive geom_point plots the mean; specify color so it does not conflict with the color call in the first geom_point

ggplot(heart,aes(x = Genotype,
                 y = Normalized.Signal))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Name,
                 shape = Replicate),
             alpha = 1.0)+
  geom_errorbar(data = heart_sum1,
                aes(ymin = Normalized.Signal-sd,
                    ymax = Normalized.Signal+sd,
                    width = 0.2))+
  geom_point(data = heart_sum1,
             size = 0.4,
             alpha = 1.0,
             color = "red")+
  xlab("Naa10 genotype")+
  ylab("NAA10 signal normalized to
       REVERT total protein stain")+
  ggtitle("NAA10 levels in Naa10
          heterozygous mutant heart")

###dplyr group data

##Unpaired t-test of NAA10 signal grouped by Genotyp

Null hypothesis: there is no mean difference in NAA10 signal between Naa10 female genotypes

Alternative: there is a difference in NAA10 signal between Naa10 female genotypes

t.test(heart$Normalized.Signal~heart$Genotype,
       paired = F,
       var.equal = FALSE)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  heart$Normalized.Signal by heart$Genotype
## t = -14.512, df = 9.9121, p-value = 5.297e-08
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group Naa10 +/- and group Naa10 +/+ is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -170525.9 -125084.6
## sample estimates:
## mean in group Naa10 +/- mean in group Naa10 +/+ 
##                74149.56               221954.80

According to Welchs two sample t-test, there is a significant difference in NAA10 signal between Naa10 female genotypes (t = -14.5, df = 9.9, p < 0.05).

##paired t-test of NAA10 signal between replicates of individual animals Null hypothesis: there is no difference in NAA10 signal of individual livers on replicate blots Alternative hypothesis: there is a difference in NAA10 signal of individual livers on replicate blots

#paired t-test because individual biological replicate was technically replicated twice

t.test(heart$Normalized.Signal~heart$Replicate,
       paired = T,
       var.equal = FALSE)
## 
##  Paired t-test
## 
## data:  heart$Normalized.Signal by heart$Replicate
## t = -0.17783, df = 5, p-value = 0.8658
## alternative hypothesis: true mean difference is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -116824.8  101706.7
## sample estimates:
## mean difference 
##       -7559.059

According to the paired t-test (t = -0.18, df = 5, p = 0.87), I fail to reject the null hypothesis. Ie, when I analyze the normalized NAA10 signal in technical replicates of each biological replicate, there is no difference in the NAA10 signal between technical replicates.
